This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with image generation and denoising. It also involves the use of neural networks, which suggests that it could also belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper proposes a novel family of GANs, which could fall under the neural networks (cs.NE) sub-category. Finally, the paper evaluates its proposed method on benchmark datasets, which suggests that it could also belong to the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
